COMMENTS ON CONDITIONS AFFECTING THIS ST: (5) General Comments on Escapement Estimation: Fence count started on 13 October 1998 when the water level was high enough to pass fish. The escapement was estimated using a Baysean Mark Recapture calculation. (2) CO Run 1 Reliability: The counting fence was opened to allow unrestricted and unenumerated coho movement past during mid November. 686 adults were marked before the fence was opened and marks were recovered through deadpitch surveys. (4) Describe basis for estimating total adults CO Run 1: Baysean mark recapture estimate. 95% CI is 5000 - 9620. Estimated 3085 adults were coded-wire tagged. (14) Flood: Higher than normal rainfall during mid November resulted in uncounted coho moving past the fence. This probably didn't have any adverse effect on egg to fry survival
